main event: A weather observer at Indian Springs AFB Nevada reported unidentified objects tracked via theodolite and radar on May 11, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were observed at altitudes estimated between 75,000 to 100,000 feet., The sighting lasted approximately four hours., A total of 27 separate objects were picked up on radar at one point., There was significant dust and high winds present during the observation., The report indicates that sightings were attributed to weather phenomena or unidentified aerial objects and not conventional aircraft.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects tracked by theodolite and radar
